Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of recovering sparse signals from low-pass projections in a domain other than Fourier, which is a problem of interest in signal processing and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing). The paper also mentions applications in holography and time-varying system identification, which suggest sub-categories cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper introduces new concepts such as the SAFT series and short-time SAFT, which may be relevant to sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
